<body>
  <h1>Building a Strong Safety Culture</h1>
  <p>A strong safety culture creates an environment where everyone feels empowered and responsible for safety. Here are some key steps to get you started:</p>

  <h2>Lay the groundwork</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Evaluate risks: Identify potential hazards and assess the risks involved.</li>
    <li>Set goals: Establish clear objectives for your safety program.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Get everyone involved</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Communication is key: Make safety a regular topic of conversation. Hold meetings, training sessions, and safety talks.</li>
    <li>Involve all levels of employees: Encourage employees to participate in safety discussions and committees.</li>
  </ul>

